<p>I wrote the following code:</p>  <pre><code>case "$2"  in  '+') ((res = $1 + $2 ));;                 '-') ((res = $1 - $2 ));; esac  echo $res </code></pre>  <p>Usage example: <code>./"*filename*" 2 + 3</code></p>  <p>If I use double parentheses,</p>  <pre><code>((res = $1 + $2 )) </code></pre>  <p>then the result gets printed. However, if I use single parentheses</p>  <pre><code>(res = $1 + $2 ) </code></pre>  <p>then nothing gets printed. What is the difference between <code>( )</code> and <code>(( ))</code>?</p>